                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">JURY DUTY</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            A full-time permanent employee who has been requested to serve on jury duty will be
                                            given a leave of absence, with pay, for a total of three (3) days of jury duty per summons.
                                            Such leave in excess of three (3) days will be unpaid. The summons or other evidence of
                                            appearance must be submitted to Company. Employees must give Company 15 days
                                            advance notice.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">VOTING PRIVILEGES</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            A full-time employee, whose scheduled work shift does not allow him/her sufficient time
                                            to vote in any state or federal election, will be granted two (2) hours of time off with pay
                                            in order to vote. To receive time off for voting, an employee must notify his/her manager
                                            and present a valid voter’s registration card. When the employee returns from voting,
                                            he/she is required to present a voter’s receipt to his/her manager.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">MILITARY LEAVE</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            Company will comply with applicable laws regarding military leaves of absence and reemployment
                                            rights. Requests for unpaid military leave should be submitted promptly and
                                            accompanied by a copy of each employee’s orders indicating the beginning and ending
                                            dates of their duty.
                                            <br />
                                            Employees on military leave are not entitled to holiday pay, insurance and other benefits.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">BEREAVEMENT LEAVE</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            Company will provide up to three (3) days of paid leave for employees should a death
                                            occur in the immediate family. The immediate family is defined as the employee’s
                                            spouse, domestic partner, children, parents. In order to be eligible, the employee may be
                                            required to provide Company with proof of death and/or relationship of the decedent to
                                            employee or spouse. If circumstances demand that additional time be taken, unpaid leave
                                            may be granted by the employee’s manager. an employee’s accrued, unused Vacation
                                            may also be used for this purpose.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">HOLIDAYS</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            Regular full-time employees will receive a day off with pay on each of the holidays
                                            specified by Company. Temporary or part-time employees are not eligible for any paid
                                            holidays. The amount of holiday pay will be determined on the basis of the employee’s
                                            current base hourly rate of pay.
                                            <br />
                                            It is currently our policy to close Company for business on the following holidays with
                                            pay:
                                        </p>
                                        <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                            <ol>
                                                <li>New Year’s Day</li>
                                                <li>Memorial Day</li>
                                                <li>Independence Day</li>
                                                <li>Labor Day</li>
                                                <li>Thanksgiving Day</li>
                                                <li>Christmas Day</li>
                                            </ol>
                                        </MudText> <br />
                                        <p>
                                            Holidays that occur during an employee’s vacation are not to be counted as vacation days
                                            taken. Employees are not eligible for holiday benefits that occur while they are on leave
                                            of absence. Further, employees must have successfully completed their Probationary
                                            Period with Company to be eligible for holiday pay.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            To be eligible for holiday pay, you must be regularly scheduled to work on the day on
                                            which the holiday is observed and must work your regularly scheduled working days
                                            immediately preceding and immediately following the holiday, unless an absence on
                                            either day is approved in advance by your supervisor or the absence is otherwise
                                            protected by law.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <i>
                                                If a holiday falls on a weekend, Company will inform you when the holiday will be
                                                observed. Ordinarily, holidays falling on a Saturday will be observed the preceding
                                                Friday; holidays falling on a Sunday will be observed the following Monday.
                                            </i>
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">EMPLOYEE GROUP INSURANCE BENEFITS</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            All regular employees regularly scheduled 30 or more hours per week will be offered
                                            health insurance which covers medical, dental, and vision care. In addition, a life
                                            insurance and Accidental death and dismemberment insurance will be offered as well. In
                                            following PPACA and its provisions therein, Company will provide 70% of the total
                                            insurance premium for each employee while each employee will need to pay the
                                            supplementary 30% of the insurance premium. Coverage for spouse and/or dependents
                                            may be added, but the employee will be responsible for 100% of the additional premium.
                                            Employees will be given the option of opting out of participating in the Company group
                                            insurance.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            All eligible employees will be offered to participate in the Company group insurance on
                                            the 1st day of the month following the completion of the 60th day of employment with
                                            Company not to exceed 90 days from the date of hire.<br />

                                            Temporary, Probationary, and part-time employees are not eligible for these benefits.
                                            This policy is only a general summary of the health care benefits offered. The details of
                                            the group insurance plans are available in the Human Resources.<br />
                                            Company reserves the right to terminate or modify the benefits it offers to its employees.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </MudExpansionPanel>

                    @*********Company Policies & Practices Section*********@
                    <MudExpansionPanel>
                        <TitleContent>
                            <MudText Typo="Typo.h5">COMPANY POLICIES & PRACTICES</MudText>
                        </TitleContent>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">MANAGEMENT/EMPLOYEE RELATIONS</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            Our managers are committed and trained to provide you with the tools and positive
                                            working environment for you to do your job to the best of your ability with minimal
                                            distractions. You will be treated with respect and dignity by all of our management
                                            personnel, and we will try our best to recognize and reward your hard work and
                                            accomplishments.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            We recognize there may be occasions for misunderstandings and problems to come up.
                                            We want to clear up these types of situations in a fair and timely manner and in order to
                                            do this we need your help in bringing them to our attention. We want you to know that
                                            “management is never too busy to be informed of work-related problems, complaints or
                                            disputes of any employee.”
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            If you have such a problem, you should promptly talk to your manager. They will listen
                                            in an open, objective and courteous manner. If the problem is not resolved to your
                                            satisfaction, you should take up the matter with the President.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Every necessary action will be taken to resolve a problem or settle a dispute in a fair and
                                            equitable manner. We recognize our employees as our most valuable resource, and we
                                            take all employee problems and complaints very seriously. No problem is too small or
                                            insignificant and each issue will be given the utmost attention and consideration.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">TEAMWORK</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            We cannot achieve our goals and provide the highest levels of service to our customers
                                            without working together as a team. Teamwork basically boils down to common courtesy
                                            and common sense. If a co-worker is overloaded and you’re not, help them in any way
                                            you can. It’s only a matter of time before they will return the favor. Pitch in to help a
                                            customer whether they are technically yours or not. If another employee hasn’t quite
                                            caught on to something and you have, ask if you may suggest another way to do it.
                                            Genuine teamwork makes for much more enjoyable and satisfying work experience and
                                            results in happier (and more generous) customers.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">CALIFORNIA TRANSPARENCY IN SUPPLY CHAINS ACT</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            The California legislature enacted the California Transparency in Supply Chains Act of
                                            2010, which became effective January 1, 2012. The purpose of the Act is to ensure that
                                            retailers and/or producers of goods disclose their efforts to eradicate slavery and human
                                            trafficking from their supply chain. Company strives for the highest level of honesty,
                                            integrity and ethics in its business practices and, has implemented policies and
                                            procedures aimed to prevent slavery and human trafficking in its supply chain.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Consistent with our commitment, Company conducts ongoing internal assessments of its
                                            direct supply chain aimed at, among other things, understanding the potential challenges
                                            in a global supply chain of the risks of human trafficking and slavery. In this regard,
                                            Company reviews available data and reports from organizations and companies dedicated
                                            to social compliance.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">WOMEN'S RIGHTS</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            Company ensures that female employees will receive equal remuneration, including
                                            benefits, equal treatment, equal evaluation of the quality of their work, and equal
                                            opportunity to fill all positions open to male employees. Pregnancy tests will not be a
                                            condition of employment, nor will they be demanded of employees. Employees will not
                                            be forced or pressured to use contraception.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">SAFETY</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            Company is committed to maintaining a safe workplace for all of our employees. The
                                            time to be conscious about safety is before an accident happens. Safety is everyone’s
                                            responsibility and is a regular, ongoing part of everyone’s job.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Employee safety and health is of paramount importance to Company. Company strongly
                                            believes that a clean, safe, and healthy working environment should be provided for all
                                            employees, not only in accordance with all applicable laws but as part of its good
                                            business practices. Safety and health are foremost consideration in all aspects of our
                                            operation. Safety and health issues are the responsibility of every employee, and no
                                            employee should perform any duty that is unsafe. Our goal is to create a work
                                            environment that is free from injuries or work-related illnesses. Meeting this goal will
                                            require the cooperation of every employee in detecting and controlling hazardous and
                                            potentially hazardous conditions.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Accidents and/or injuries must be reported to your supervisor immediately, regardless of
                                            how minor they appear to be, so that Company may take corrective action as soon as
                                            possible. Failure to report your own injury may disqualify you from receiving Workers'
                                            Compensation benefits, in addition to subjecting you to discipline pursuant to Company
                                            policies.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            All employees are required to observe safety rules and to help ensure that Company is a
                                            safe and orderly place to work. Employees must remember the following basic rules: (1)
                                            Observe common safety rules; (2) do not behave reckless or carelessly on Company
                                            property; (3) keep your work area clean and orderly; (4) do not operate equipment or
                                            work in an abusive, unsafe, or improper manner. Employees who violate any of these
                                            rules or who act in an unsafe environment will be subject to discipline, up to and
                                            including termination.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Company will also have a safety plan in place, which will be more detailed for the
                                            factory environment. All employees should become familiar with that plan and should
                                            direct any questions to management or Human Resources.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">ACCIDENT AND EMERGENCY SITUATIONS</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            Report all accidents, no matter how minor they seem, to the manager on duty. In the
                                            event of an emergency, like an apparent injury or chocking situation, notify a manager
                                            immediately.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">CRIME AND ROBBERY</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            If you are ever involved in a robbery, DO NOT RESISTS! Statistics show that people,
                                            who resist, are three times more likely to be injured than people who do not resist. The
                                            safety of you, your fellow employees and customers are our highest priority. Don’t be a
                                            hero, always cooperate fully and do not resist!
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">DRESS CODE</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            You should always be neat and clean in accordance with generally accepted personal
                                            hygiene standards. Employees are required to follow all safety regulations regarding
                                            shoes or apparel for their work area.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Moderation in dress and grooming is required. No extreme hairstyles or excessive
                                            makeup or jewelry is allowed.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Office staff members are expected to wear appropriate business attire. Direct any
                                            questions regarding dress code to Hunan Resource.<br />
                                            Failure to comply may subject you to disciplinary action.<br />
                                            Employees who need a reasonable accommodation because of religious beliefs,
                                            observances or practices should contact Human Resources with day-to-day personnel
                                            responsibility and discuss the need for accommodation.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">CELL PHONE/SMART PHONE POLICY</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            Employees are prohibited from using their cell phones or smart phones while on duty to
                                            make or receive personal calls, emails, text messages or other similar electronic
                                            communications unless there is an emergency. Employees who need to use their personal
                                            cell phone or smart phone may only do so during meal/break periods. Usage of personal
                                            cell phone or smart phone including texting during business hours will lead to
                                            termination of employment without warning. Employees also may not use cell phones
                                            containing audio or video recording devices or cameras in the following work areas that
                                            Company has designated as confidential, secure or private, unless the employee is
                                            engaged in protected activity related to improving the terms and conditions of his or her
                                            employment, such as documenting health and safety issues. This restriction applies to the
                                            following areas: design room, sample/pattern room, production control room, Human
                                            resource Room, QA/QC area.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Company may, in its sole discretion, issue cell phones to certain employees. It is our
                                            expectation that cell phone use be conducted in the same manner as the use of any other
                                            company property or equipment, including regular telephones. Cell phones should be
                                            used with care and use should be limited to business purposes. Company will review
                                            telephone records for any inappropriate or personal use of a company cell phone.
                                            Company strongly discourages employees from using cellular phones while driving a
                                            vehicle in the course of business. Any injuries, accidents, traffic violations or any other
                                            result of an employee’s use or misuse of a cell phone will be at the employee’s expense.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">COMPLIANCE WITH VEHICULAR LAWS</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            All employees who drive vehicles for Company must follow all vehicular laws in the
                                            various states of employment including but not limited to mandatory seat belt use laws,
                                            speed limit laws, cell phone usage laws and any and all other rules of the road. This
                                            regulation applies whether the individual is driving a company vehicle or their personal
                                            vehicle on Company. Any employee who receives parking tickets, speeding tickets
                                            and/or other traffic citations while on Company shall be personally responsible for the
                                            same and Company will take no responsibility for any accident or injury occurring as a
                                            result of a violation of the Vehicle Code.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Continued employment by any person who drives a company vehicle or their personal
                                            vehicle on Company requires a continuously valid California Driver’s License. Company
                                            may require employees who drive company vehicles to produce, on request, a valid
                                            certified copy of their driving record from the Department of Motor Vehicles. Company
                                            may terminate or reassign employees who were hired as drivers and who display a poor
                                            driving record.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">SMOKING POLICY</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            No smoking of any kind is permitted inside any the Company’s buildings or showrooms.
                                            Smoking may take place only in designated smoking areas, if any, outside of the
                                            Company’s facilities. The smoking prohibition applies to all smoking devices, including,
                                            but not limited to, the use of electronic smoking devices, such as electronic cigarettes,
                                            pipes, hookahs, and vaping devices. Moreover, the Company will strictly enforce any
                                            state and/or municipal laws concerning designated smoking areas.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">VISITORS IN THE WORKPLACE</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            For safety, insurance, and other business considerations, only authorized visitors are
                                            allowed in the workplace. Employees must inform their manager prior to making
                                            arrangements for a visitor to come on the premises.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">COMPANY SOCIAL EVENTS</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            On occasion, Company may sponsor or arrange social and recreational functions. At all
                                            such social and recreational functions, employee participation is entirely voluntary. Such
                                            voluntary functions are not considered work time. Employees, at such functions, are not
                                            compensated for their time in attendance and are not covered by workers compensation
                                            or similar insurance. Company will not be liable or responsible for any injuries to
                                            employees while attending any such voluntary social functions. Further, Employees are
                                            responsible for their own behavior and actions, and Company will not be responsible for
                                            nor indemnify or hold the employee harmless from any damage or injury caused by the
                                            Employee at any such function.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">COMPANY PROPERTY</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            All Company property must be used for business purposes only. In addition, employees
                                            should take care not to engage in willful and/or negligent destruction of the Company’s
                                            equipment, facilities, or other property. Employees who are found to have engaged in
                                            willful or grossly negligent activity resulting in damage to Company property shall be
                                            charged for all such damage. Company equipment and/or facilities may not be used for
                                            non-business reasons at any time except with the express written authorization of
                                            management. Likewise, company’s equipment may not be removed from the Company
                                            premises without the express written authorization of the employee’s Department Head.
                                            Any Company equipment or property issued to an employee must be returned upon
                                            request of Company, or at the time of termination.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">ELECTRONIC COMMUNICATION</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            Many job positions at Company rely on the use of its computer systems and electronic
                                            mail for executing day-to-day responsibilities. It is expected that all employees will use
                                            computer hardware and software and electronic mail in accordance with their intended
                                            and lawful business purposes. In this regard, the following rules have been established to
                                            govern the use of computers, software, electronic mail, and the internet in the workplace.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <b><u>Computer Systems</u></b> <br />
                                            <ol>
                                                <li>
                                                    Operation or utilization of Company computer resources for purposes other than
                                                    those related to the conduct of business is prohibited, except on a minimal basis,
                                                    and then in accordance with all principles of ethics and good, common sense.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>
                                                    Allowing another person to access the Company's computer resources using your
                                                    password is prohibited unless approved by management.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>
                                                    No employee may install, operate, or access software programs on the Company's
                                                    computer resources without prior written authorization from management and
                                                    proper software licensing.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>
                                                    Every employee is expected to fully cooperate with all efforts to maintain the
                                                    Company's computer systems.
                                                </li>
                                            </ol>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <b><u>E-mail and the Internet</u></b>
                                            <br />
                                            Electronic mail can greatly enhance the quality and efficiency of communication among
                                            employees, clients, and other involved in our business. But e-mail can also be misused,
                                            with potentially serious consequences.
                                            <br />
                                            You should respect the rights and sensitivities of recipients and potential recipients or
                                            viewers and should ensure that all e-mail messages reflect a professional image. It is
                                            expected that you will use common sense and good judgment when using e-mail and
                                            computer systems.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Data, information, messages, or communications that are transmitted or stored on the
                                            Company's computer system are the records and property of Company. Employees
                                            should bear in mind that Company may access messages sent to or by employees in the
                                            ordinary course of business at any time, without notice.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Employees should operate within the Company's public relations, code of conduct, antiharassment,
                                            and anti-discrimination guidelines. Employees are expressly prohibited from
                                            sending any messages or materials containing obscene, profane, lewd, derogatory, or
                                            otherwise potentially offensive language or images. Violation of these principles will
                                            result in discipline, up to and including termination.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Access to the Internet is a privilege that may be revoked by Company at any time and for
                                            any reason. Employees may not use Company resources to obtain, view, download, or
                                            otherwise gain access to, distribute, or transmit obscene, pornographic, abusive, or
                                            otherwise objectionable materials. Employees may not use the Internet for any unlawful
                                            or unethical purposes, including but not limited to traffic that violates a copyright or trade
                                            secret law, distribution of non-Company advertising, propagation of computer worms or
                                            viruses, attempts to make unauthorized access to another network, or for recreational
                                            games.
                                        </p>
                                    </MudText>
                                </ChildContent>
                            </MudExpansionPanel>
                            <MudExpansionPanel>
                                <TitleContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">SOCIAL MEDIA NETWORK POLICY</MudText>
                                </TitleContent>
                                <ChildContent>
                                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                                        <p>
                                            Social Media Network policies are not to discourage an employee from utilizing social
                                            media but rather to clarify the respective rights and responsibilities of Company and its
                                            employees to these new networking opportunities. These policies also protect the privacy,
                                            confidentiality, and interests of Company and our current and potential products,
                                            employees, partners, customers, and competitors. These policies and guidelines are
                                            intended to apply to work-related sites, products, references, personnel, and issues and
                                            are not meant to infringe upon your personal interaction or commentary online.
                                            These policies emphasize that the computer system is to be used for the purpose of the
                                            Company’s business only.
                                        </p>
                                        <b><u>Employee Code of Conduct for Online Communications</u></b>
                                        <br />
                                        <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Style="display:list-item">
                                            The Social Media Network Policy applies to multi-media, social networking
                                            websites, blogs, and wikis for both professional and personal use. Internet
                                            postings should not disclose any information that is confidential or proprietary to
                                            Company or to any third party that has disclosed information to Company.
                                        </MudText>
                                        <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Style="display:list-item">
                                            Company encourages you to write knowledgeably, accurately, and to use
                                            appropriate professionalism. Despite disclaimers, your Web interaction can result
                                            in members of the public forming opinions about Company and its employees,
                                            partners, and products.
                                        </MudText>
                                        <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Style="display:list-item">
                                            Honor the privacy rights of our employees by seeking their permission before
                                            writing about or displaying internal company matters that might be considered to
                                            be a breach of their privacy and confidentiality.
                                        </MudText>
                                        <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Style="display:list-item">
                                            You may not sell any product or service that would compete with any of
                                            Company's products or services without permission in writing from the president.
                                            This includes, but is not limited to training materials, books, brochures, products,
                                            and freelance writing. If in doubt, speak with your manager and/or the president.
                                        </MudText>
                                        <br />
                                        <b><u>Employee Code of Conduct for Company Representation in Online Communications</u></b>
                                        <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Style="display:list-item">
                                            If you mention on any website or media platform, Company and/or our current
                                            and potential products, employees, partners, customers, and competitors, identify
                                            that you are an employee of Company and that the views expressed on are yours
                                            alone and do not represent the views of Company. Company reserves the right to
                                            request removal or modifications of any media or content that reflects poorly on
                                            Company
